<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EEC) No 2989/82 of 9 November 1982 on the granting of aid for the consumption of butter in Denmark, Greece, Italy and Luxembourg </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 2989/82 abi andmise kohta v&otilde;i tarbimiseks Taanis, Kreekas, Itaalias ja Luksemburgis 9. november 1982 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 804/68 of 27 June 1968 on the common organization of the market in milk and milk products (1), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 1183/82 (2), and in particular Article 12 (2) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 27. juuni 1968. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 804/68 piima- ja piimatooteturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (1) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1183/82, (2) eriti selle artikli 12 l&otilde;iget 2, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the situation on the Community butter market is characterized by large stocks and it is therefore advisable to increase the consumption of butter by all appropriate means; </inglise>
<eesti> olukorda &uuml;henduse v&otilde;iturul iseloomustavad suured varud, mist&otilde;ttu on soovitatav suurendada v&otilde;i tarbimist k&otilde;ikide asjakohaste vahenditega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the reduction of final consumer prices is an efficient means of attaining this objective; whereas, to this end, the Commission envisages the adoption of an ad hoc measure based on Article 6 (7) of Regulation (EEC) No 804/68 involving an additional reduction in the price of butter bought for direct consumption in view of the Christmas and New Year holidays; </inglise>
<eesti> l&otilde;plike tarbijahindade alandamine on t&otilde;hus vahend selle eesm&auml;rgi saavutamiseks; selleks kavandab komisjon m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 804/68 artikli 6 l&otilde;ike 7 p&otilde;hjal ajutise meetme vastuv&otilde;tmist, mis seisneb otsetarbimiseks ostetava v&otilde;i hinna t&auml;iendavas alandamises, pidades silmas j&otilde;ulusid ja aastavahetust; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the implementation of the abovementioned measure presents particular problems in Denmark, Greece, Italy and Luxembourg; whereas, in fact, the butter markets in these Member States are characterized by very low or non-existent public stocks and by very small quantities under private storage contracts; whereas, in order to avoid placing consumers in these Member States at a disadvantage, as compared with consumers in the other Member States, provision should be made for subsidizing butter in Denmark, Greece, Italy and Luxembourg on the same conditions as the butter sold in the other Member States in the framework of the said measure; </inglise>
<eesti> eespool nimetatud meetme rakendamine p&otilde;hjustab Taanis, Kreekas, Itaalias ja Luksemburgis teatavaid probleeme; tegelikult iseloomustab k&otilde;nealuste liikmesriikide v&otilde;iturgusid riigi v&auml;ga v&auml;ike v&otilde;i olematu varu ning eraladustuslepingute alusel ladustatava v&otilde;i v&auml;ga v&auml;ikesed kogused; k&otilde;nealuste liikmesriikide tarbijate ebasoodsasse olukorda sattumise v&auml;ltimiseks v&otilde;rreldes teiste liikmesriikide tarbijatega tuleks s&auml;testada v&otilde;i subsideerimine Taanis, Kreekas, Itaalias ja Luksemburgis samadel tingimustel kui k&otilde;nealuse meetme raames m&uuml;&uuml;dava v&otilde;i subsideerimine teistes liikmesriikides; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Denmark and Luxembourg make use of the provisions of Council Regulation (EEC) No 1269/79 of 25 June 1979 on the marketing of reduced-price butter for direct consumption (3), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 1186/82 (4); whereas the measure provided for in this Regulation has to take into account the aid granted in pursuance of the said Regulation, </inglise>
<eesti> Taani ja Luksemburg rakendavad n&otilde;ukogu 25. juuni 1979. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1269/79 (otsetarbimiseks etten&auml;htud v&otilde;i alandatud hindadega turustamise kohta, (3) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1186/82 (4)) s&auml;tteid; k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud meedet tuleb v&otilde;tta arvesse abi andmisel vastavalt k&otilde;nealusele m&auml;&auml;rusele, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Aid shall be granted in Denmark, Greece, Italy and Luxembourg for the direct consumption of butter. </inglise>
<eesti> Taanis, Kreekas, Itaalias ja Luksemburgis antakse abi v&otilde;i otsetarbimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The aid is hereby fixed at 130 ECU per 100 kilograms for Greece and Italy and at 85 ECU per 100 kilograms for Denmark and Luxembourg. </inglise>
<eesti> Abi summaks m&auml;&auml;ratakse 130 ek&uuml;&uuml;d 100 kilogrammi kohta Kreekas ja Itaalias ning 85 ek&uuml;&uuml;d 100 kilogrammi kohta Taanis ja Luksemburgis. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> The detailed rules for the application of this Regulation shall lay down, in particular, a time limit for the packaging of the butter in small packets, the maximum amount of butter which may be eligible for the aid referred to in Article 1, and provisions guaranteeing that the butter will be consumed in the Member State for which it is intended. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaldamise &uuml;ksikasjalikes eeskirjades s&auml;testatakse eelk&otilde;ige v&otilde;i v&auml;ikepakkidesse pakkimise t&auml;htaeg, artiklis 1 osutatud abi saamise tingimustele vastava v&otilde;i maksimumkogus ning s&auml;tted, mis tagavad liikmesriigis v&otilde;i tarbimise etten&auml;htud otstarbel. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub selle Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas avaldamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 9 November 1982. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 9. november 1982 </eesti>
